+# Contract - Kinly Market Scenario Surfaces v1.0
+
+## Purpose
+
+Define the canonical behavior for scenario-specific marketing surfaces hosted
+under `/kinly/market/*`.
+
+These pages tailor recognition-first copy to specific shared-living situations
+without changing Kinly's core positioning, safety boundaries, or routing model.
+
+## Canonical Namespace (Normative)
+
+All scenario landing pages MUST live under:
+
+- `/kinly/market/<scenario_slug>`
+
+Scenario previews MAY also be resolved through:
+
+- `/kinly/general?entry=<scenario_slug>`
+
+When both routes are available, `/kinly/market/<scenario_slug>` is canonical.
+
+## Scenario Descriptor (Normative)
+
+Each scenario MUST define:
+
+- `scenario_slug`: URL-safe slug used in `/kinly/market/<scenario_slug>`
+- `entry_alias`: query alias accepted by `/kinly/general?entry=...`
+- `page_key`: outreach tracking key for scenario page analytics
+- `status`: `active` | `deprecated`
+
+Constraints:
+
+- `scenario_slug` and `entry_alias` MUST be lowercase kebab-case.
+- `page_key` MUST be lowercase snake_case.
+- `page_key` MUST be stable once published.
+- `scenario_slug`, `entry_alias`, and `page_key` MUST be unique.
+
